3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper studies decentralized inference systems, which are often used in social and information networks. 
4. cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper deals with parallel and tandem networks, which are relevant to distributed computing. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper explores connections between the sufficiency principle and some distributed source coding problems, which are relevant to multimedia applications.
